04:32.171 --> 04:37.017
So this morning, we're going to be taking a look in Philippians three.

04:38.199 --> 04:44.146
Paul here, he's in prison and he's writing this letter to the church of Philippi.

04:44.322 --> 04:47.887
A lot of Paul's letters, it's half instructing the people and half yelling at some other people.

04:48.588 --> 05:11.538
And one of the things he's fighting against here and what we're gonna read is there's this whole group of Jewish Christians, it's called some Judaizers, it's kind of a slam on him, but where they're coming in and it's kind of like wherever Paul's going and he's planning a church and he's doing something, when he leaves they come in and they start to try and tell

05:12.066 --> 05:39.954
you know, these new converts, and these aren't Jewish, Krishna, these are the Gentiles, and they go in and they tell them, well, really you need to be, you need to be like us first, you need to become a Jew first, you need to follow all these laws and all this stuff, you need to be circumcised and do all these things, and it's getting a little frustrating for Paul, you know, as we'll see in some of his language that he uses here, he's not happy with these people, and it's because what they're doing is slowing down the work, you know,

05:40.098 --> 05:50.650
One of the things they're doing, first off, is they're trying to make becoming a Jew in the way you live and how you look and stuff more important than Christ.

05:51.371 --> 05:57.198
And it's getting in the way of that, in which Paul's getting very frustrated because he's trying to put, no, no, no, it's not about that stuff, it's about Christ.

05:57.218 --> 06:07.410
And the other thing, just the practical thing is, is when they're saying this stuff, it's slowing down the growth of the church, which makes sense, because if you know anything about circumcision,

06:07.586 --> 06:10.992
you can understand that that's a little bit of a hard sell at the end of the membership meeting.

06:13.216 --> 06:24.317
Everyone comes in, you know, and you go through, okay, you know, we're asking to be a member here, you believe in that, okay, do this, and we're looking for people to, you know, you want people to volunteer and, okay, that's a little bit of my time, but I can do that.

06:24.337 --> 06:26.060
You know, you can get along with everything until at the end they go.

06:26.080 --> 06:31.250
And then the last thing, can you come up forward and chop off the tip of your finger?

06:32.674 --> 06:33.275
Excuse me.

06:34.837 --> 06:38.321
I did not see that in the fine print on here on the brochure.

06:38.341 --> 06:42.006
You know, it's like, well, you know, we're still a church shop and we'll get back with you.

06:42.026 --> 06:43.868
I mean, that would obviously slow down.

06:44.769 --> 06:45.310
And think about it.

06:45.330 --> 06:47.553
I mean, this is two, this is before modern medicine.

06:47.573 --> 06:51.318
I mean, this was no, there's no Novocaine.

06:51.378 --> 06:57.005
There's no, you know, you're not going under for anything as just you and the blade and the Lord.

06:57.125 --> 06:58.687
I mean, that's not comfortable.

06:58.947 --> 06:59.348
Okay.

07:00.209 --> 07:01.010
And it's like,

07:01.346 --> 07:04.231
He's so positive and so frustrated at these people.

07:04.952 --> 07:07.295
So he's going to slam them a little bit.

07:07.496 --> 07:17.592
And then he starts talking about how in his life, he had these things and his value system gets flipped upside down.

07:17.652 --> 07:24.082
And as I was thinking about this, I thought, of course, first,

07:24.738 --> 07:29.064
You know, it comes into my head as some cultural movie references, often where my brain goes.

07:29.104 --> 07:32.429
And I thought, you know, it's kind of like a post-apocalyptic sense.

07:32.449 --> 07:36.454
You've never seen a movie like Mad Max or something like that, if so, center, just kidding.

07:37.095 --> 07:39.098
But it's this post-apocalyptic world, right?

07:39.118 --> 07:40.720
And everything's different.

07:40.781 --> 07:43.725
And apparently, people are going to wear a lot of leather.

07:44.285 --> 07:45.487
That's what I gather from that.

07:45.547 --> 07:50.354
You know, if the World War III starts to start loading up on leather now, because that's like what you're going to wear, OK?

07:50.466 --> 07:53.690
And the economy system is all upside down.

07:53.770 --> 07:59.137
Things that are important now are, it's like water, you know, if you control water, like, oh, that's the most precious thing.

07:59.557 --> 08:01.760
Gold and money, all that stuff's garbage.

08:01.780 --> 08:05.064
And because everything's been turned upside down, the economy's been turned upside down.

08:05.605 --> 08:10.951
And you kind of think of a different, I thought, you know, there's been times I know in my life where that's happened.

08:11.432 --> 08:19.442
You know, I thought about how, you know, when my wife and I, when we first got married and we're building this life, I mean, you know, we're going after,

08:19.618 --> 08:22.082
You know, career and trying to get money so we can do things.

08:22.583 --> 08:27.751
One thing we did not consider of much value because we had such an abundance of it was freedom.

08:29.254 --> 08:31.096
We could do kind of whatever we wanted to.

08:31.137 --> 08:35.023
We could decide, you know, at any given moment, hey, let's go out of town for a few days.

08:35.063 --> 08:39.169
Yeah, okay, and just get up and go, assuming you didn't have to work or something.

08:39.190 --> 08:46.962
And then we have these beautiful little children that come into our lives, love them, gifts from God, absolutely yes, but then we realize

08:48.482 --> 08:49.503
We don't have any freedom.

08:51.105 --> 08:54.168
And now that becomes a resource that we go after greatly.

08:54.448 --> 08:59.294
In fact, the resource we were going after money will now give you money if you will give us some freedom.

09:00.555 --> 09:00.855
Right?

09:00.915 --> 09:04.599
And you do and you find that babysitter, you hunt for them.

09:04.640 --> 09:12.368
You know, you search for them through the night to find that one babysitter you can trust is so great and the kids, you know, they don't terrorize the kids and the kids like them.

09:12.388 --> 09:18.034
And if you find that babysitter, it's like you try to enter them into witness protection program, right?

09:18.882 --> 09:20.884
Like babysitter protection programs, someone should invent that.

09:21.305 --> 09:25.189
And you find a babysitter, we'll sequester them, we'll take their name off the record, so we'll be able to find them.

09:26.130 --> 09:30.174
Because you want that resource, so whenever you go to that, you can have it because I want my freedom.

09:31.256 --> 09:32.997
I need two hours on the weekend, please.

09:34.439 --> 09:36.802
And everything just kind of changes in your life.

09:37.302 --> 09:39.925
And so that's a little bit of what Paul's talking about.

09:39.945 --> 09:44.870
He has this encounter with Christ and kind of see how everything in his life that he thought was important.

09:44.911 --> 09:45.992
No, that's not now important.

09:46.012 --> 09:46.833
Now this is important.

09:47.794 --> 09:48.114
All right.

09:49.570 --> 09:52.175
Now I did tell a story, dear wife of mine.

09:53.096 --> 09:53.918
I don't know if I ever told you.

09:53.938 --> 10:02.994
I ever tell you that once when I was watching our oldest, as fathers do when we're watching a child, we put them in front of the TV and we fall asleep.

10:04.737 --> 10:06.841
And I was awoken to a thud.

10:06.861 --> 10:08.483
I ever tell you that.

10:11.148 --> 10:12.210
I feel like the

10:12.354 --> 10:13.756
You know, that's the statute.

10:13.776 --> 10:15.098
I mean, he's 17 now.

10:15.138 --> 10:15.518
He's good.

10:15.558 --> 10:17.401
He's way smarter than I have ever been.

10:17.481 --> 10:18.683
So clearly, I didn't damage him.

10:18.703 --> 10:20.706
But I totally woke up to him hitting the floor.

10:21.607 --> 10:23.209
She's between me and you, buddy.

10:23.249 --> 10:23.770
Don't tell anyone.

10:24.351 --> 10:26.413
And I wasn't sure why I said that.

10:26.434 --> 10:27.715
I don't think that had any value.

10:27.735 --> 10:30.980
But I figured I'd come clean because it's out there on the internet.

10:31.000 --> 10:33.523
Someone's going to ask, so I hear your son struggling.

10:33.543 --> 10:34.204
It's funny, my dad.

10:35.346 --> 10:37.088
He was watching the first service actually.

10:37.108 --> 10:37.529
He texted me.

10:37.549 --> 10:41.234
He's like, well, I think it's safe to say no one will ask you to watch their children.

10:41.666 --> 10:43.429
Fair enough, all right, mission accomplished.

10:43.449 --> 10:50.239
That's part, that's step one of what I wanted to get along is don't ask me to watch your children because obviously I will fall asleep and they may fall off of things, all right?

10:50.960 --> 10:53.263
But you start realizing kids are harder to kill than you realize.

10:54.525 --> 10:54.766
They are.

10:55.046 --> 10:58.631
Now, I'm not saying you try to, but I grew up, I was the youngest.

10:58.712 --> 11:00.013
I did not grow up around babies.

11:00.054 --> 11:05.562
My baby sat one time for my uncle, Bishop Ed, and three boys, little girl.

11:05.582 --> 11:06.643
I feel like they have told this story before.

11:07.084 --> 11:09.167
I forgot there was a little girl there.

11:09.187 --> 11:11.090
I took the three boys and just left the house at one point.

11:13.570 --> 11:14.752
That's a lot of math.

11:14.772 --> 11:15.774
Three kids, four kids.

11:15.794 --> 11:16.555
Who can tell?

11:16.575 --> 11:18.879
I got the majority of them.

11:19.720 --> 11:20.802
Still a winning percentage.

11:21.122 --> 11:25.650
But yeah, he gave me a, I came back and finally he got a hold of me, gave me a call.

11:25.690 --> 11:26.491
What's going on?

11:26.792 --> 11:27.313
Where were you?

11:27.333 --> 11:28.434
I'm like, what are you talking about with the kids?

11:28.855 --> 11:29.696
Where's Elizabeth?

11:31.640 --> 11:32.862
Because I just got a call from the neighbors.

11:32.882 --> 11:33.743
She went over to the neighbors.

11:34.044 --> 11:34.985
See, she's fine.

11:35.947 --> 11:37.970
It's, they're harder to get rid of than you think.

11:39.202 --> 11:40.243
So yes, don't let me want you kids.

11:40.263 --> 11:41.324
Let's get into the scripture here.

11:41.404 --> 11:42.485
All right, let's get into this.

11:42.565 --> 11:43.606
Let's read some scripture.

11:44.247 --> 11:45.388
Let me confessing my sins.

11:45.588 --> 11:52.656
So here Paul is, and he's a little frustrated with these Judaizers coming in, talking about circumcision.

11:52.676 --> 11:59.282
So he writes to the church in Philippi, he says here, chapter three, verse one, further my brothers and sisters, rejoice in the Lord.

11:59.963 --> 12:05.148
It is no trouble for me to write the same things to you again, and it is a safeguard to you.

12:05.168 --> 12:06.770
So he's repeating something he said before.

12:07.138 --> 12:11.703
He said, watch out for those dogs, those evil doers, those mutilators of the flesh.

12:11.743 --> 12:13.745
He's talking about these Judaizer guys.

12:14.366 --> 12:22.635
He says, for it is we who are the circumcision, we who serve God by his spirit, who boast in Christ Jesus and who put no confidence in the flesh.

12:23.676 --> 12:25.758
So you can say, he is not happy with these guys.

12:26.179 --> 12:27.280
He calls them dogs.

12:28.501 --> 12:34.127
And you go through any research that back then in their culture, the dogs, they were scavengers.

12:35.268 --> 12:36.850
They were the ones that came behind you

12:37.250 --> 12:38.972
ate the scraps and this and that.

12:39.053 --> 12:53.433
So he's kind of likening that imagery to these guys, because in his word, I go and I plant a church, and then I leave, and then these scavenger dogs come in and they're scavenging, they come into the church, well, yeah, but are you circumcised?

12:53.613 --> 12:54.134
Do you have this?

12:54.154 --> 12:54.775
Do you have that?

12:54.815 --> 12:55.857
He's like, go away, shoot, dog!

12:56.998 --> 12:57.819
And he slams them.

12:59.021 --> 13:02.706
He calls them evil doers.

13:02.727 --> 13:05.170
In other words, what they're doing is pulling the church

13:05.282 --> 13:06.724
away from God.

13:06.744 --> 13:08.206
He's not bringing them towards them.

13:08.226 --> 13:14.053
He's sitting there, instead of focusing in on Christ, like, no, no, no, it's about following the laws and how you look.

13:14.073 --> 13:17.577
And if you've been circumcised, all these things, he's going after those things.

13:17.877 --> 13:21.602
He says they're doing evil because they're taking you away from God.

13:23.204 --> 13:26.648
And then here he calls them those mutilators of the flesh.

13:27.549 --> 13:30.072
Now that's a translation of the Greek word.

13:30.093 --> 13:34.578
And then now when you look at the Greek, you find out that Paul was actually making a pun.

13:34.818 --> 13:44.653
And the Greek word for mutilation, mutilate, sounds almost like the Greek word for circumcised.

13:45.434 --> 13:46.696
So he's doing this on purpose.

13:47.097 --> 13:48.659
He's like, oh, what you're saying is circumcised?

13:48.699 --> 13:50.001
No, no, no, it's actually this.

13:50.282 --> 13:51.283
Just change it up a little bit.

13:51.324 --> 13:52.565
You're actually mutilators.

13:53.307 --> 14:00.438
And that's a big slam to them because circumcision for these people, we do it today just for a medical thing or this or that.

14:01.179 --> 14:03.282
It's a holy thing for them.

14:03.650 --> 14:05.473
This is why there's so adamant about that.

14:05.493 --> 14:07.396
You know, I was trying to think like, what could we liken it to today?

14:07.416 --> 14:14.287
And the other thing I thought was like how we tend to be with our communion, especially if you grew up, you know, in Catholicism and you grew up with a Catholic direct communion.

14:14.327 --> 14:14.968
That's the deal.

14:16.390 --> 14:21.298
And it'd be like someone coming in instead of referring to communion or Eucharist, they said, oh, I got to go up there and get my Jesus cracker.

14:23.061 --> 14:23.281
Right?

14:23.942 --> 14:29.010
Maybe you've made that joke, but that's like an offensive thing of like, cause it takes all of,

14:29.122 --> 14:33.807
The supernatural takes all the God, it takes all of what is going on in that moment and throws it out.

14:34.027 --> 14:35.088
And this is what Paul is saying.

14:35.148 --> 14:37.090
He's saying, you're sitting there saying you're doing circumcision.

14:37.110 --> 14:38.111
It's not circumcision.

14:38.612 --> 14:43.857
It's not this you're doing it because of this covenant that God made with Abraham.

14:44.277 --> 14:44.998
That's not what it's about.

14:45.238 --> 14:47.240
What you're doing is you're just mutilating flesh.

14:47.541 --> 14:49.643
In other words, it has no spiritual value.

14:51.204 --> 14:53.447
And he's hammering them and slamming them.

14:54.648 --> 14:56.850
And then he goes on and he's explained, he's like, no, no, see,

14:57.634 --> 14:59.637
What true circumcision is now.

15:00.799 --> 15:04.324
He says, it's those of us who serve God.

15:05.126 --> 15:07.129
It's we are the circumcision.

15:07.149 --> 15:14.540
You know, we who serve who follow God by his spirit, who boast that we have a confidence in Christ, but not in any human ritual, but in Christ.

15:15.742 --> 15:18.086
We put no confidence in the flesh.

15:20.209 --> 15:22.353
And see, it's something the circumcision here is talking about.

15:22.373 --> 15:25.778
There's something that happens inside of us when we have faith in Christ.

15:26.850 --> 15:30.936
And then Paul goes on to talk about the flesh.

15:31.297 --> 15:36.725
He's referring to human nature, pride, action, and the things that these guys are trying to make them do.

15:36.765 --> 15:41.552
And he's slamming these guys for what they're doing.

15:41.592 --> 15:42.814
And I look at it.

15:43.054 --> 15:52.268
Sometimes when you can't hold yourself up to the standard that someone else does, instead of just being saying, I can't hold up to the standard.

15:52.288 --> 15:53.570
You just make fun of the other person.

15:54.892 --> 15:56.434
A common example would be,

15:56.738 --> 16:07.191
You know, if you're playing sports and you lose, most people can have a difficult time just saying, oh, the better team won, right?

16:07.852 --> 16:08.873
It's usually that they cheated.

16:09.854 --> 16:10.976
You know, the refs were no good.

16:12.017 --> 16:12.818
And that's the refs fault.

16:12.918 --> 16:13.599
Ah, this is that.

16:13.639 --> 16:14.901
It's like, no, no, no.

16:14.921 --> 16:15.101
Right.

16:15.782 --> 16:18.745
Sometimes I've had this conversation with my sons, but we've all done it.

16:18.765 --> 16:19.346
I've done it.

16:19.842 --> 16:22.766
You know, get beat in some, oh yeah, you just beat me because of this or because of that.

16:22.926 --> 16:25.129
And it's, you know, we sort of slam them.

16:25.149 --> 16:27.893
We kind of put them down because they're better than us.

16:29.295 --> 16:36.264
So you could look at this and when you're reading this and Paul wants to make sure here, whoa, whoa, whoa, I'm not slamming these people because it's so hard what they're saying to do.

16:36.905 --> 16:39.488
Because they're putting these standards up and it's just too much for me to do.

16:40.690 --> 16:44.255
And he says this, he says that he puts no confidence in the flesh.

16:44.515 --> 16:49.682
He finishes that sentence by saying, though I myself have such reason for confidence.

16:51.490 --> 17:03.348
You know, he's shows in here and he's about to show how you want to talk about holding up to those big ideals of things they're saying that they're going after.

17:03.649 --> 17:06.112
Dude, I was a rock star with what they're talking about.

17:06.833 --> 17:08.656
And he goes in and he explains this here.

17:08.716 --> 17:14.185
He says, if someone else thinks that they have reasons to put confidence in the flesh, I have more.

17:15.747 --> 17:16.929
He says, I want to talk about circumcision.

17:16.969 --> 17:20.274
