19:44.636 --> 19:45.898
So don't talk to me about zeal.

19:46.819 --> 19:47.780
I get these guys.

19:48.100 --> 19:49.362
I was there.

19:49.442 --> 19:51.485
been there, done that, perfected it.

19:51.766 --> 19:53.228
I was what they wished they could be.

19:53.648 --> 19:54.830
In other words, it's just a mic drop.

19:55.932 --> 20:00.759
This isn't a thing of like, I'm just upset because they're holding these standards we can't hit to.

20:02.182 --> 20:06.368
But now we're going to see how something happens in him.

20:08.171 --> 20:10.935
And he has a change in his values.

20:11.656 --> 20:12.978
His value system changes.

20:14.914 --> 20:16.316
Because he's going through it and he's talking about this stuff.

20:16.336 --> 20:18.738
And when you look at it practically, you can take, well, what do I take from this?

20:18.778 --> 20:33.695
I mean, it means for me, whenever I'm called in to do something with Christ, I'm putting a situation and there's a way I can do things the way I think they're done in my value system and go after those things, or I can choose to go Christ.

20:34.376 --> 20:35.977
I need to choose Christ.

20:39.181 --> 20:43.666
Because he says this, he says, whatever gains,

20:44.994 --> 20:47.897
were to me, I now consider a loss for Christ's sake.

20:49.499 --> 21:01.493
In other words, it's like if you run a business or do accounting, you know, you want to see how the business is doing, you have a profit and loss statement, and you take all your profits, all your gains, and you compare them against all your losses, right?

21:02.414 --> 21:04.116
And you know what all the things, all the gains are giving you this.

21:04.136 --> 21:05.858
So in our lives, we do this.

21:06.579 --> 21:08.901
There are things we consider gains, things we go after.

21:08.941 --> 21:11.024
We need to go after this, we need to achieve that.

21:11.044 --> 21:13.106
If I'm this kind of person, if I do that,

21:13.890 --> 21:15.532
This is a game, this is what I need to go after.

21:16.193 --> 21:17.935
And that's what he said his whole life was.

21:18.376 --> 21:21.059
Those gains, not only did he go after those gains, he perfected those gains.

21:21.980 --> 21:23.502
And he says, I now consider them loss.

21:23.722 --> 21:27.487
I now have taken all those things in the gains, and I moved them over into the loss category.

21:30.190 --> 21:37.259
And he says, the reason he does this, what is more, I consider everything a loss because of the surpassing worth of knowing Christ Jesus, my Lord.

21:38.281 --> 21:42.546
For whose sake I have lost all things, I consider them garbage.

21:43.362 --> 21:44.924
The Greek word there is scuba.

21:44.984 --> 21:49.008
And if you've been around long enough and remember back in the day, my dad has talked about what scuba means.

21:49.609 --> 21:52.151
Pretty sure he did a deep series dive.

21:52.192 --> 21:54.234
And I'm just understanding the definition of scuba.

21:55.956 --> 21:58.198
Garbage is about the nicest possible translation.

21:58.338 --> 21:59.119
And it's not just my dad.

21:59.159 --> 22:03.344
It's because you read all the theologians and the scholars, they go through this.

22:03.384 --> 22:06.647
They say, well, yeah, the Greek word for that is garbage is about the nice way.

22:06.667 --> 22:07.068
You could say it.

22:07.128 --> 22:08.109
Dung is another way.

22:08.990 --> 22:09.891
Poop, crap.

22:09.911 --> 22:10.551
And it keeps getting.

22:10.571 --> 22:12.253
I think you know where I'm going.

22:12.473 --> 22:13.074
OK.

22:13.186 --> 22:17.051
It's BS, basically, is what the actual translation is there.

22:17.071 --> 22:19.735
He is saying, I did all of these things.

22:19.895 --> 22:29.367
I perfected the thing everyone wishes, and I consider it something you should throw in the toilet and flush down, because of the surpassing worth of knowing Christ Jesus.

22:30.869 --> 22:40.722
He says, I consider them scuba that I may gain Christ and be found in Him, not having a righteousness on my own that comes from the law, but that

22:41.026 --> 22:45.632
which is through faith in Christ, the righteousness that comes from God on the basis of faith.

22:47.435 --> 22:52.241
Like I said, his whole P&L statement, his own prophet and loss, it's mixed now.

22:52.802 --> 22:55.526
He takes what once was considered loss, which is Christ.

22:56.127 --> 23:02.515
Because right, he was going out there trying to crucify people, kill them, persecute the church for people who are going out there and following Christ.

23:03.016 --> 23:03.737
He's like, oh, what?

23:03.757 --> 23:05.039
I used to consider that loss.

23:06.281 --> 23:07.282
That's now my gain.

23:08.098 --> 23:11.042
and all the other stuff in my life, I consider gaining, I throw that in loss.

23:11.323 --> 23:21.859
He's saying, the reason for this is because I don't want to stand and think that I have, my worth comes from what I've just accomplished, that my worth in Christ, my view in God is just because of things that I've done.

23:23.782 --> 23:24.983
Because he's kind of perfected that.

23:25.064 --> 23:28.569
He's like, you know, I actually was so good at that, I have to just throw them out.

23:30.392 --> 23:37.362
And I thought about that, yeah, you know, I think sometimes it's when we're in the best spots of our lives,

23:37.890 --> 23:42.477
when things are going to be great, we're accomplishing things and our relationships are good, our jobs are going good things.

23:42.838 --> 23:51.551
That's probably sometimes the hardest time to really make a tough decision to follow Christ because we kind of think we're doing okay.

23:51.571 --> 23:53.154
So we're not looking for God.

23:53.174 --> 23:58.582
Tell me, because when things go bad in your life, right, when things are going tough, Lord help me.

24:00.345 --> 24:06.194
And you look for Him and you seek Him, but as I was looking at I was like, man, sometimes when things are going well and my life is going good,

24:06.434 --> 24:08.697
I need to keep reminding myself, I still need God.

24:08.717 --> 24:15.685
This is kind of part of what is nice, but if you join in a letter, you take time in the season of finding, looking in there, what's going on?

24:16.146 --> 24:17.688
How do I need to make room for God in my life?

24:17.708 --> 24:23.254
Because I don't want it to be about me and I feel good and confident because I'm a good person and I've done the right things.

24:23.915 --> 24:25.958
My faith needs to be in Christ Jesus.

24:29.582 --> 24:32.145
He says this, he says, I want to know Christ.

24:33.467 --> 24:36.050
Yes, to know the power of his resurrection.

24:36.610 --> 24:41.455
and participation in his sufferings, becoming like him in his death.

24:42.477 --> 24:45.120
And so somehow attaining to the resurrection from the dead.

24:46.962 --> 24:52.868
He's saying much like Christ, I wanna make sure that there's almost a sense of suffering a little bit.

24:53.009 --> 25:01.738
He kinda keeps himself in this suffering thing because he knows that it's in that, that he knows his reliance has to be on Christ.

25:01.979 --> 25:04.882
This is sort of part of the idea of what you think of when you fast something.

25:05.154 --> 25:05.374
Right?

25:05.675 --> 25:11.920
When we fast, when we give up something, when we remove something out of our life, it messes with us, you know?

25:12.361 --> 25:13.862
It should hurt a little bit.

25:14.143 --> 25:20.489
And the reason it hurts a little bit is because, you know, you're just reminding yourself, I could have, there's nothing, there's nothing evil in it.

25:20.509 --> 25:22.190
You give up chocolate, so I will chocolate's evil.

25:23.732 --> 25:30.679
It's the idea is just reminding yourself, no, I really want this, but I'm not going to because I need God more.

25:32.140 --> 25:34.322
And Paul's saying he's doing this with everything he had.

25:35.202 --> 25:36.144
And he's throwing it out.

25:37.987 --> 25:41.514
And he's saying, it's because he wants to be like Christ to join in the suffering.

25:42.055 --> 25:52.594
He says, not that I have already obtained all of this or have already arrived at my goal, but what I do is I press on to take hold of that for which Christ Jesus took hold of me.

25:53.730 --> 26:01.661
Brothers and sisters, I do not consider myself yet to have taken hold of it, but one thing I do, I forget what is behind and I strain towards what is ahead.

26:01.822 --> 26:07.790
I press on toward the goal to win the prize for which God has called me, heavenward in Christ Jesus.

26:09.272 --> 26:18.405
In other words, Paul sustains these sufferings, these loss, these things that he could have put confidence in, these precious things that he had gained, and they weren't awful things.

26:18.425 --> 26:21.810
You hear him going on and hammering

26:22.114 --> 26:23.596
of these guys talking about circumcision.

26:23.616 --> 26:26.220
He wasn't like anti-circumcised, he just hated it.

