God's given us things, talents, and abilities that were not just viewing God through the lens of those things first, but let's him convert.

29:15.624 --> 29:16.946
God, how do you want me to use this?

29:17.026 --> 29:18.948
How can you be real in my family?

29:18.968 --> 29:22.312
What do you want me to do with my job and these things I've done?

29:22.552 --> 29:23.113
Help me see it.

29:25.135 --> 29:25.416
Amen?

29:26.657 --> 29:26.937
Amen.

29:28.319 --> 29:28.699
All right.

29:29.500 --> 29:34.406
As we close out here, we move into our time of communion.

29:34.426 --> 29:45.138
As we do every Sunday, and I love this, it gives us a chance as we come together to examine ourselves, to take account of our little prophet in law statement.

29:45.794 --> 29:47.736
and say, God, what am I getting wrong in this thing?

29:47.756 --> 29:50.639
Help me to see it, right?

29:50.659 --> 30:08.959
And so as we go through, just as having to bow their heads, and I'm gonna say this prior, and as we do this, just do look inwardly, ask God to point out, if you look for those things that He's speaking to you that the Holy Spirit is pointing out, things that you need to maybe let go of the grip of a little bit and hang on more tightly to Christ.

30:10.280 --> 30:12.082
And during this time as well,

30:12.226 --> 30:15.730
You're a person who's never really accepted Jesus Christ as your Lord and Savior.

30:15.750 --> 30:21.437
Take a time now as we pray, as we transition into communion, to ask Him to come in and be Lord of your life.

30:24.061 --> 30:37.157
So with those in mind, let's pray, Heavenly Father, before we partake of the bread and the cup this morning, in obedience to the scriptures, we now pause to look inward to examine ourselves.

30:39.460 --> 30:41.202
God, help us to see things we've gotten

30:41.698 --> 30:46.886
out of whack, things that we may be considered too high of a prophet that we need to let go of a little bit.

30:48.769 --> 31:09.682
So Lord, if we have sinned against you and thought word or deed by what we have done or by what we have left undone, if we have not loved you with our whole heart, if we have not loved our neighbors as ourselves, for the sake of your beloved son, Jesus Christ, who gave himself as a sacrifice for our sins, have mercy on us, forgive us of all our sins,

31:10.050 --> 31:22.044
strengthen us in all goodness and by the power of your Holy Spirit, keep us in eternal life that we may delight in your will and walk in your ways to the glory of your name.

31:24.109 --> 31:24.370
Amen.

